Khan et al. [94] implemented a combination between Jaya and TLBO to form a new algorithm called the JLBO algorithm. The new algorithm is used for optimum sizing of a standalone hybrid PV-wind-battery based on minimizing the TAC of the system. In this simulation, LPSP is employed to evaluate the reliability. The optimization results indicated that PV/wind/battery is the most cost effective system with TAC values of $ 66542, $ 60752, $ 50247, $ 43046, and $ 34464 at LPSPmax\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
